<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771057>
    dc:description "FIGURE 37. Female T5, anal fimbria. Scale=0.5 mm. A) Triangular (A. peritomae, BBSL487552). B) Reduced (A. exigua, BBSL487552). The latter species is exceptional in that most of the fimbrial setae are appressed over the rim, rather than erect." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771057/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

